/--
**Golod-Shafarevich inequality.**

For every prime `p` and every nontrivial finite `p`-group `Q`, the generator
rank and relation rank satisfy

```
d(Q)^2 < 4 r(Q).
```

Here `d(Q)` is the generator rank, defined as the minimal size of a generating
set of `Q`, and `r(Q)` is the relation rank, defined as the dimension of
`H^2(Q; F_p)` as a vector space over the finite field `F_p`.

Reference: NSW, Theorem 3.9.7; Serre, Chapter I, Appendix 2, Theorem 1.

Lean-to-English translation notes: in the Lean file, the condition that `Q` is
a finite `p`-group is expressed by the typeclass assumptions
`[Group Q] [TopologicalSpace Q] [IsTopologicalGroup Q] [DiscreteTopology Q]
[Finite Q]`, followed by `IsPGroup p Q`.

This setup is used because `generatorRank` and `relationRank` are stated for
topological groups. Thus finite `p`-groups are viewed as topological groups
with the discrete topology. In this setting, topological generation agrees with
ordinary generation, and continuous cohomology agrees with ordinary group
cohomology.
-/
