/-- **Golod-Shafarevich inequality** (Neukirch-Schmidt-Wingberg 3.9.7,
Serre I.App.2 Theorem 1). Not yet in Mathlib. -/
axiom golod_shafarevich_inequality : Hyp_GolodShafarevichInequality

/-- **Shafarevich relation-rank bound** (Mayer 5.1; Koch 11.5+11.8).
Not yet in Mathlib. -/
axiom shafarevich_relation_rank_bound : Hyp_ShafarevichRelationRankBound

/-- **Erdős problem 90** (disproved).

Conjecture: for every $\varepsilon > 0$, eventually $\nu(n) < n^{1+\varepsilon}$.
(This is the $\nu(n) \le n^{1+o(1)}$ upper bound; the original problem asks for
the sharper bound $\nu(n) \le n^{1+O(1/\log\log n)}$, which is stronger and so
also fails.)

Disproof: `main_theorem` produces a constant $\delta > 0$ with
$\nu(n) \ge n^{1+\delta}$ for infinitely many $n$. Take $\varepsilon = \delta$
in the conjecture — eventually $\nu(n) < n^{1+\delta}$, but infinitely many $n$
have $\nu(n) \ge n^{1+\delta}$, contradiction. -/
theorem erdos_90 :
    ¬ ∀ ε : ℝ, 0 < ε →
        ∀ᶠ n in Filter.atTop, (νn n : ℝ) < (n : ℝ) ^ (1 + ε) := by
  intro hconj
  obtain ⟨δ, hδpos, hinf⟩ :=
    main_theorem golod_shafarevich_inequality shafarevich_relation_rank_bound
  obtain ⟨N, hN⟩ := Filter.eventually_atTop.mp (hconj δ hδpos)
  obtain ⟨n, ⟨_, hνn⟩, hnN⟩ := hinf.exists_gt N
  exact absurd hνn (not_le.mpr (hN n hnN.le))

